1. Create Workflow

POST http://localhost:8090/api/workflows
Content-Type: application/json

Request Body:

{
  "name": "deployment-pipeline",
  "tasks": [
    {
      "id": "build",
      "type": "script",
      "dependsOn": [],
      "config": {
        "command": "mvn clean package"
      },
      "retryPolicy": {
        "attempts": 3,
        "delaySeconds": 2
      },
      "timeoutSeconds": 300
    },
    {
      "id": "test",
      "type": "script",
      "dependsOn": ["build"],
      "config": {
        "command": "mvn test"
      },
      "timeoutSeconds": 300
    },
    {
      "id": "deploy",
      "type": "http",
      "dependsOn": ["test"],
      "config": {
        "url": "http://localhost:9090/deploy",
        "method": "POST",
        "headers": {
          "Authorization": "Bearer token123"
        },
        "body": "{\"version\": \"1.0\"}"
      }
    }
  ]
}

2. Get Workflow
GET http://localhost:8090/api/workflows/{workflow-id}

3. Start Execution
POST http://localhost:8090/api/workflows/{workflow-id}/executions

4. Check Execution Status
GET http://localhost:8090/api/executions/{execution-id}

5. Cancel Execution (optional)
POST http://localhost:8090/api/executions/{execution-id}/cancel
Replace {execution-id} with the execution ID. No request body.

6. Approval Workflow (special flow with approval gate)
First, create a workflow with an approval task:


{
  "name": "approval-demo",
  "tasks": [
    {
      "id": "build",
      "type": "notification",
      "dependsOn": []
    },
    {
      "id": "manual-approval",
      "type": "approval",
      "dependsOn": ["build"],
      "config": {
        "timeoutMinutes": 5
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "deploy",
      "type": "notification",
      "dependsOn": ["manual-approval"]
    }
  ]
}


After creating and starting, when you check status, manual-approval will show RUNNING (blocked on latch).

Resolve approval (approve):

POST http://localhost:8090/api/executions/{execution-id}/approval
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "taskId": "manual-approval",
  "approved": true,
  "approver": "john.doe@example.com",
  "reason": "Looks good for production"
}

Then check status again — deploy should now proceed.

Resolve approval (reject):

{
  "taskId": "manual-approval",
  "approved": false,
  "approver": "security-team@example.com",
  "reason": "Security review failed"
}

Test Sequence:
✅ POST /api/workflows → Create workflow, save ID
✅ GET /api/workflows/{id} → Verify it was stored
✅ POST /api/workflows/{id}/executions → Start execution, save execution ID
✅ GET /api/executions/{id} → Poll until SUCCESS/FAILED
✅ (Optional) POST /api/executions/{id}/cancel → Test cancellation on a different execution
✅ (Optional) POST /api/executions/{id}/approval → Test approval flow

mvn spring-boot:run